    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta</strong>, reserving a cup of the starchy pasta water and set aside until later</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chicken </strong>and the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4 min further</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use to 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> tomato paste </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reduce to a medium-high heat and add your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then pour in the <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has reduced to a pasta sauce-like consistency</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and remove from the heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir through a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped chives </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>to the sauce and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken pasta with tomatoes and chilli</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken pasta with tomatoes and chilli</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chives</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
